## Helpful Macros
### P1  Setup Macro
Discord breaks the macro. See this post to get it: [ Vault Knights PlayStation Macro](
https://na.finalfantasyxiv.com/lodestone/character/27408312/blog/5009018/)

This is also the orientation of markers you'll use in P5 PlayStation 2. It looks like this in-game:
```
D △   T X   T □
D O         D O
D □   H X   H △
```
### Spammable Meteor Dodge Macro
Spam this to perform the cursed four hour meteor dodge. 
```
/mlock
/merror off
/automove on <wait.1>
/automove off
/echo
/echo
/echo
/echo
/echo
/echo
/echo
/echo
/echo
/echo
/echo
```
### P5 Limit Break Macro
You can use this macro to limit break without facing your target; as a phys range with proper positioning, this will allow you to limit break four meteors instead of three.
```
/mlock
/macroicon "Limit Break"
/autofacetarget off
/ac "Limit Break"
/autofacetarget on
```
### P6 Rot Macro
Create four macros using this format, one for each of your DPS, and click it when you see which job receives rot.
```
/p Rot1 Tank1 Tank2 Melee Ranged <se.2>
/micon "Ninja" classjob
```
### P6 Wroth Flames Macros
The following spread/stack/no debuff macros are for use in Wroth Flames. These macros are not compatible with automarker, and rely on each player pressing the correct one when debuffs go out.
*Spread*
Click this if you receive a spread to indicate your spread order.
```
/mk attack <me> <wait.25>
/mk clear <me>
/micon attack enemysign
```
*Stack*
Click this if you receive a stack to indicate you need to be stacked with. Aim for the ignore marker with the same number as you (1 with 1, 2 with 2).
```
/mk bind <me> <wait.25>
/mk clear <me>
/micon bind enemysign
```
*No Debuff*
Click this if you receive no debuff. You should stand on the same number bind as you have (1 with 1, 2 with 2).
```
/mk ignore <me> <wait.25>
/mk clear <me>
/micon ignore enemysign
```
## 6-1-1 Mit Plan Macros
**Transition, every Akh Morn, and every Gigaflare require Kerachole/Sacred Soil.** The correct timing for an Akh Morn kera/SS is immediately after the second trinity in exaflares; this will ensure it catches all of akh morn and will be up for the subsequent giggleflare.
```
==========================
SCH/AST 6-1-1:
/p transition: HoL, missionary, samba, improv, collective, spreadlo
/p akh morn 1: feint 1, fey illum, neutral,  addle
/p gigaflare 1: expedient, seraph, feint 2, collective
/p akh morn 2: samba
/p gigaflare 2: HoL, missionary, feint 1, collective, spreadlo, addle, macro
/p akh morn 3: expedient, seraph, neutral, feint 2, fey illum
========================== 
```
```
==========================
SCH/WHM 6-1-1:
/p transition: HoL, missionary, samba, improv, spreadlo
/p akh morn 1: temp, feint 1, fey illum, addle
/p gigaflare 1: expedient, seraph, feint 2
/p akh morn 2: samba, bell
/p gigaflare 2: HoL, missionary, spreadlo, feint 1, addle
/p akh morn 3: temp, expedient, seraph, feint 2, barrier, fey illum
========================== 
```
```
==========================
SCH/SGE 6-1-1:
/p transition:  HoL, samba, improv, spreadlo
/p akh morn 1: missionary, feint 1, panhaima, physis, fey illum
/p gigaflare 1: expedient, addle, seraph, feint 2, holos
/p akh morn 2: samba, physis
/p gigaflare 2: HoL, missionary, feint 1, spreadlo
/p akh morn 3: expedient, addle, seraph, panhaima, feint 2, physis, holos, fey illum
========================== 
```
```
==========================
SGE/AST 6-1-1:
/p transition: HoL, missionary, samba, improv, barrier, collective (USE PERSONALS)
/p akh morn 1: panhaima, feint 1, addle, physis
/p gigaflare 1: neutral, feint 2, holos, collective
/p akh morn 2:  samba, barrier, physis
/p gigaflare 2: HoL, missionary, feint 1, addle, collective, macro
/p akh morn 3: panhaima, neutral, feint 2, holos, physis
========================== 
```
```
==========================
SGE/WHM 6-1-1:
/p transition: HoL, missionary, samba, improv, barrier (USE PERSONALS, IF NO RDM USE HOLOS)
/p akh morn 1: panhaima, temp, feint 1, physis
/p gigaflare 1: holos, feint 2, addle
/p akh morn 2: samba, bell, physis
/p gigaflare 2: HoL, missionary, feint 1
/p akh morn 3: panhaima, temp, barrier, holos, feint 2, addle, physis
========================== 
```
## __3-3-2 Mit Plans Macros__
**Transition, every Akh Morn, and every Gigaflare require Kerachole/Sacred Soil.** The correct timing for an Akh Morn kera/SS is immediately after the second trinity in exaflares; this will ensure it catches all of akh morn and will be up for the subsequent giggleflare.
```
==========================
SCH/AST:
/p transition: HoL, missionary, samba, improv, collective, spreadlo
/p akh morn 1: barrier, feint 1, addle, fey illum
/p gigaflare 1: expedient, seraph, feint 2, collective, neutral
/p akh morn 2: HoL, missionary, samba
/p gigaflare 2: feint 1, addle, collective, spreadlo
/p akh morn 3: expedient, seraph, neutral, feint 2, barrier, fey illum
========================== 
```
```
==========================
SCH/WHM:
/p transition: HoL, missionary, samba, improv, spreadlo
/p akh morn 1: temp, feint 1, addle, barrier, fey illum
/p gigaflare 1: expedient, seraph, feint 2
/p akh morn 2: HoL, missionary, samba, bell
/p gigaflare 2: spreadlo, feint 1, addle
/p akh morn 3: temp, expedient, seraph, feint 2, barrier, fey illum
========================== 
```
```
==========================
SGE/AST:
/p transition: HoL, missionary, samba, improv, barrier, collective (USE PERSONALS, IF NO RDM USE HOLOS)
/p akh morn 1: panhaima, feint 1, addle, physis
/p gigaflare 1: feint 2, holos, collective, neutral
/p akh morn 2: HoL, missionary, samba, barrier, physis
/p gigaflare 2: feint 1, collective, addle, pneuma
/p akh morn 3: panhaima, neutral, feint 2, holos, physis
========================== 
```
```
==========================
SGE/WHM:
/p transition: HoL, missionary, samba, improv, barrier (USE PERSONALS, IF NO RDM USE HOLOS)
/p akh morn 1: panhaima, temp, feint 1, physis, addle
/p gigaflare 1: holos, feint 2, pneuma
/p akh morn 2: HoL, missionary, samba,  barrier, bell, physis
/p gigaflare 2: feint 1, addle
/p akh morn 3: panhaima, temp, holos, feint 2, physis, pneuma
